    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix m3ap_direction2String function indexing error\n\n### Summary\nThe `m3ap_direction2String` function in `m3ap_handler.c` was returning incorrect strings due to improper array indexing. When processing M3AP messages, the function would return an empty string instead of the expected direction description.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/M3AP/m3ap_handler.c`: Fixed array indexing in `m3ap_direction2String` function and made it static to prevent linking conflicts\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen M3AP messages are processed and the direction string is logged, instead of showing \"Originating message\", \"Successfull outcome\", or \"UnSuccessfull outcome\", an empty string is displayed in the log messages. This can be observed in the M3AP logging output when M3 setup or MBMS session messages are exchanged.\n\nThe issue occurs because the function was incorrectly mapping `pdu.present` values to array indices, causing a mismatch between the M3AP PDU direction and the returned string description.\n\n"
}